```latex
\documentclass[tikz,border=10pt]{standalone}
\usepackage{pgfplots}
\pgfplotsset{compat=1.18}
\usepackage{amsmath}

\begin{document}

\begin{tikzpicture}
  \begin{scope}[local bounding box=plots]
    \begin{loglogaxis}[
      width=0.475\textwidth,
      grid=both,
      grid style={line width=.1pt, draw=gray!30},
      major grid style={line width=.2pt, draw=gray!70},
      xmin=0, xmax=1,
      ymin=1e-8, ymax=1,
      xlabel={Time ($t$)},
      ylabel={Changes},
      legend style={at={(0.5,-0.15)}, anchor=north, draw=none, fill=gray!5, nodes={scale=0.8, transform shape}}
    ]
      \addplot [dashed, color=red!70!black] coordinates {(0,0.5) (1,0.5)};
      \addplot [dashed, color=blue!70!black] coordinates {(0,0.1) (1,0.1)};
      \addplot [dashed, color=cyan!70!black] coordinates {(0,0.000001) (1,0.000001)};
      \addplot [dashed, color=black] coordinates {(0,0.00000001) (1,0.00000001)};
      \addplot [dashed, color=black] coordinates {(0,1) (1,0.00000001)} node [pos=0, left] {$O(h^4)$};
      \legend{L2 energy (N=100), L2 energy (N=1000), Hamiltonian energy (N=100), MHK Example 77, Hamiltonian energy (N=1000), MHK Example 7}
    \end{loglogaxis}

    \begin{loglogaxis}[
      width=0.475\textwidth,
      at=(plots.right of south east),
      anchor=left of south west,
      grid=both,
      grid style={line width=.1pt, draw=gray!30},
      major grid style={line width=.2pt, draw=gray!70},
      xmin=1e-3, xmax=1e0,
      ymin=1e-10, ymax=1,
      xlabel={Time ($t$)},
      ylabel={$\ell_2$ error},
    ]
      \addplot [domain=1e-3:1e0, thick, color=cyan!70!black] {x*x*x*x};
      \addplot [domain=1e-3:1e0, thick, color=blue!70!black] {5e-10*x*x*x*x};
      \addplot [domain=1e-3:1e0, thick, color=green!70!black] {2e-9*x*x};
      \addplot [domain=1e-3:1e0, thick, color=black] {5e-2*x*x};
      \addplot [domain=1e-3:1e0, thick, color=red!70!black] {1e-2};
    \end{loglogaxis}
  \end{scope}
\end{tikzpicture}

\end{document}
```

### Explanation:
- The code uses the `pgfplots` package to create two log-log plots side by side.
- The first plot shows changes over time for L2 energy and Hamiltonian energy, as well as for different examples (MHK Example 77 and MHK Example 7), with a legend explaining each line.
- The second plot shows the convergence of the $\ell_2$ error at $t = 1$ for different methods, with the error curves clearly marked.
- Grid lines are included with specified styles to match the original image.
- The axis labels and legends are placed according to the original image for clarity.

